  "dct_description_sm": [
    "Europe NUTS 1 Demographics is a polygon theme representing areas of aggregated socioeconomic and demographic information at the NUTS 1 level for Europe. NUTS 1 units have an average population between three million and seven million people. NUTS (Nomenclature des Unites Territoriales Statistiques) refers to the Nomenclature of Territorial Units for Statistics. For more information: http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/ramon/nuts/home_regions_en.html."
